The cDNA position and protein positional change is always related to a particular transcript and protein isoform. This is also evident from the "transcrtipt overview" which list both gene and transcript in addition to the amino acid or cDNA change. The purpose of "transcript overview" is to provide a quick summary of the "likely" most important changes for refSeq transcripts. We can list both cDNA and amino acid change there if you would like, although this information is present in the more informative transcript table.
When you order Sanger or look in the transcript table you have HGNC_Symbol;RefSeq_Transcript;ExonNumber;cDNA;AminoAcid, which is usually enough information to order primers. Would you like to have any additional information presented?

